quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  76,23,It is We who sent down the Quran upon you—a gradual revelation
  76,24,"So be patient for the decision of your Lord, and do not obey the sinner or the blasphemer among them"
  76,25,"And mention the Name of your Lord, morning and evening"
  76,26,"And for part of the night, prostrate yourself to Him, and glorify Him long into the night"
  76,27,"As for these: they love the fleeting life, and leave behind a Heavy Day"
  76,28,"We created them, and strengthened their frame; and whenever We will, We can replace them with others like them"
  76,29,"This is a reminder; so whoever wills, let him take a path to his Lord"
  76,30,"Yet you cannot will, unless God wills. God is Knowing and Wise"
  76,31,"He admits into His mercy whomever He wills. But as for the wrongdoers, He has prepared for them a painful punishment"